Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now CAPE TOWN - The Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises continues its inquiry into mismanagement of state funds at Eskom. The power utility's head of generation Matshela Koko gives evidence on Wednesday. Koko’s presentation was distributed on Tuesday, and he's implicating former board chair Zola Tsotsi in illicit payments. He claims he was suspended for failing to make the payments to a Japanese company. Koko and former chief financial officer, Anoj Sigh were asked to resign in the interest of the company. Singh resigned on Monday, but it's not yet clear if Koko will follow suit. eNCA